1
00:00:53,345 --> 00:00:55,931
Did Mama tell you?

2
00:01:01,395 --> 00:01:03,564
Sorry.

3
00:01:06,776 --> 00:01:09,361
It was an accident, son.

4
00:01:10,029 --> 00:01:14,867
Is Teacher Sam mad at me?

5
00:01:16,243 --> 00:01:18,537
No. Never!

6
00:01:19,789 --> 00:01:23,375
Teacher Sam loved you very much.

7
00:01:24,084 --> 00:01:26,837
She would've gotten mad
if she had found out

8
00:01:26,921 --> 00:01:28,839
you were blaming yourself.

9
00:01:30,174 --> 00:01:33,052
She knew it was all an accident.

10
00:01:33,135 --> 00:01:34,929
You didn't mean to do it.

11
00:01:40,726 --> 00:01:42,686
So, let's just keep this to ourselves.

12
00:01:43,729 --> 00:01:45,523
Don't tell anyone else.

13
00:01:49,944 --> 00:01:52,404
Only our family should know.

14
00:03:48,062 --> 00:03:49,730
Good day, Mr. Carpio.

15
00:03:50,773 --> 00:03:51,815
What do you need?

16
00:03:52,441 --> 00:03:54,818
We'd like to invite you
to the police station.

17
00:03:56,403 --> 00:03:57,529
You and Mrs. Carpio.

18
00:03:59,782 --> 00:04:00,741
What for?

19
00:04:01,909 --> 00:04:04,036
About Sam Ignacio's death.

20
00:04:05,746 --> 00:04:08,582
Isn't that case already closed?
Her brother already confessed.

21
00:04:10,876 --> 00:04:12,586
We found new evidence.

22
00:04:14,046 --> 00:04:16,882
We've found Sam Ignacio's phone.

23
00:04:18,425 --> 00:04:20,386
And we've seen some things from it

24
00:04:20,928 --> 00:04:22,346
that I believe...

25
00:04:23,722 --> 00:04:26,141
only you can shed light on.

26
00:04:33,941 --> 00:04:34,942
All right, then.

27
00:04:36,902 --> 00:04:37,736
We'll come.

28
00:04:40,948 --> 00:04:42,366
I'll go tell my wife.

29
00:05:49,683 --> 00:05:52,186
Here we are, Professor Carpio.

30
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:54,980
This way, Mr. Carpio.

31
00:05:59,151 --> 00:06:01,695
Wait, why… why do we have to be separated?

32
00:06:02,196 --> 00:06:04,782
I believe your statements
will remain consistent

33
00:06:04,865 --> 00:06:06,533
even if you're interrogated
separately, won't they?

34
00:06:11,413 --> 00:06:12,873
It's fine, Anton.

35
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:15,167
There's nothing wrong with it.

36
00:06:31,183 --> 00:06:33,936
We created printouts of text messages

37
00:06:34,019 --> 00:06:36,814
between Sam Ignacio
and the person she referred to as B.

38
00:06:43,237 --> 00:06:44,613
Here's B's message.

39
00:06:45,239 --> 00:06:46,532
"Still have a migraine?"

40
00:06:47,366 --> 00:06:49,284
Sam Ignacio's response.

41
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:55,916
B answered.

42
00:07:02,005 --> 00:07:04,925
Here's another text from Sam Ignacio.

43
00:07:06,135 --> 00:07:09,680
"I know we already agreed
to be just friends.

44
00:07:11,557 --> 00:07:14,309
Still, I just want to tell you
that I love you.

45
00:07:14,852 --> 00:07:17,104
You don't have to give me an answer.

46
00:07:19,148 --> 00:07:20,774
I just want you to know."

47
00:07:22,693 --> 00:07:24,361
B replied.

48
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:27,156
"I also want you to know that I love you.

49
00:07:27,948 --> 00:07:29,867
Even if this is as far as we could get."

50
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:38,208
This is the registered phone number

51
00:07:38,292 --> 00:07:40,752
based on B's contact details.

52
00:08:21,793 --> 00:08:24,504
You and B share the same contact number...

53
00:08:25,255 --> 00:08:28,217
on Sam Ignacio's phone.

54
00:08:32,137 --> 00:08:34,389
Your last messages to her

55
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:37,726
were on the night of August 10.

56
00:08:38,352 --> 00:08:40,187
On the night of her death.

57
00:08:42,022 --> 00:08:44,399
You sent a message to her

58
00:08:44,483 --> 00:08:48,362
that you'd meet her at your favorite spot.

59
00:08:48,445 --> 00:08:50,572
Based on your last message,

60
00:08:50,656 --> 00:08:52,157
you were already at the parking area.

61
00:09:04,628 --> 00:09:07,631
We also retrieved this from Sam's phone.

62
00:09:08,340 --> 00:09:10,050
It was taken that night.

63
00:09:20,894 --> 00:09:24,064
When we first asked you

64
00:09:24,147 --> 00:09:26,733
about the last time you saw Sam,

65
00:09:26,817 --> 00:09:28,986
you gave us a different answer.

66
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,419
It's true that Sam and I loved each other.

67
00:09:49,381 --> 00:09:51,258
I didn't tell you the truth

68
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:53,176
because I wasn't ready...

69
00:09:55,929 --> 00:09:57,306
for my kids

70
00:09:59,933 --> 00:10:01,226
and for Anton to know.

71
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:04,229
I already knew about them.

72
00:10:04,896 --> 00:10:07,232
I found out a few days before Sam died.

73
00:10:09,526 --> 00:10:10,736
Okay, then.

74
00:10:14,281 --> 00:10:15,490
Are you all right?

75
00:10:16,241 --> 00:10:18,243
You sound different.

76
00:10:21,496 --> 00:10:24,082
Okay. By the lighthouse.

77
00:10:27,002 --> 00:10:28,378
All right. Take care.

78
00:10:36,011 --> 00:10:37,095
You going out?

79
00:10:38,472 --> 00:10:39,514
No.

80
00:10:51,443 --> 00:10:53,653
Is that why you went to Los Pollos?

81
00:10:53,737 --> 00:10:55,822
I know what this looks like.

82
00:10:55,906 --> 00:10:58,033
And it's clearly not in my favor.

83
00:10:58,825 --> 00:11:00,744
But Sam and I just talked.

84
00:11:02,579 --> 00:11:03,872
As Jackie's husband,

85
00:11:03,955 --> 00:11:05,916
I told her to stay away from my wife

86
00:11:05,999 --> 00:11:08,585
and never show her face
to my family again.

87
00:11:09,836 --> 00:11:11,254
Does your wife know about this?

88
00:11:12,798 --> 00:11:15,092
I just recently found out

89
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:17,594
that Anton knew about Sam and me.

90
00:11:18,553 --> 00:11:19,638
Just recently.

91
00:11:20,305 --> 00:11:22,265
Why didn't you tell your wife about it?

92
00:11:25,936 --> 00:11:27,104
Mr. Carpio.

93
00:11:27,813 --> 00:11:29,231
I don't know.

94
00:11:30,273 --> 00:11:31,316
What about you, Chief?

95
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,151
If you were in my situation,

96
00:11:33,235 --> 00:11:34,778
which one's easier?

97
00:11:34,861 --> 00:11:36,905
To tell the person
your wife loves to go away...

98
00:11:38,365 --> 00:11:42,494
or to beg your wife to choose you
knowing she won't?

99
00:11:42,577 --> 00:11:45,747
I chose my kids because I can't hurt them.

100
00:11:51,461 --> 00:11:53,463
Is that why Sam was leaving?

101
00:11:58,051 --> 00:12:01,388
I met with her that night to say goodbye.

102
00:12:02,139 --> 00:12:03,974
Did you have an argument?

103
00:12:06,810 --> 00:12:09,688
Did she force you to come with her?

104
00:12:09,771 --> 00:12:11,314
Not at all.

105
00:12:13,692 --> 00:12:17,612
Sam and I both agreed
that we can't continue

106
00:12:17,696 --> 00:12:19,948
whatever it is that we have between us.

107
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:23,618
We broke up on good terms.

108
00:12:26,580 --> 00:12:29,249
So, Ms. Ignacio told you
that she was leaving.

109
00:12:31,209 --> 00:12:33,670
Why did you have to threaten her?

110
00:12:33,753 --> 00:12:37,132
I just wanted to make sure
that she'd keep her word.

111
00:12:39,885 --> 00:12:41,928
Did you know that they
would meet at the lighthouse

112
00:12:42,012 --> 00:12:44,222
on the night Sam Ignacio died?

113
00:12:45,515 --> 00:12:46,516
No.

114
00:12:47,601 --> 00:12:48,935
He didn't.

115
00:12:49,478 --> 00:12:52,355
Anton didn't know that Sam and I
were going to meet that night.

116
00:12:52,439 --> 00:12:53,565
He didn't.

117
00:12:54,608 --> 00:12:57,861
Do you know what this is
making me think, Mr. Carpio?

118
00:12:57,944 --> 00:13:00,864
You had a hunch
that your wife would meet up

119
00:13:01,364 --> 00:13:03,074
with Ms. Ignacio at the lighthouse.

120
00:13:03,158 --> 00:13:04,910
So you followed them.

121
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:07,037
As you have suspected,

122
00:13:07,662 --> 00:13:09,664
you caught them together.

123
00:13:09,748 --> 00:13:12,167
You got mad, saw red,

124
00:13:12,250 --> 00:13:15,170
then pushed the poor teacher
off the cliff.

125
00:13:17,339 --> 00:13:20,133
And because your wife
blames herself for everything,

126
00:13:20,217 --> 00:13:22,969
she couldn't do anything but cover up

127
00:13:23,053 --> 00:13:25,388
your murder of Ms. Ignacio.

128
00:13:32,687 --> 00:13:34,773
That's a nice story, Chief.

129
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:38,360
The problem is…

130
00:13:39,611 --> 00:13:41,196
you have no evidence.

131
00:13:45,825 --> 00:13:47,410
Chief, we all know...

132
00:13:48,119 --> 00:13:50,580
that Sam Ignacio's case is a dead end.

133
00:13:56,378 --> 00:14:00,840
Were you with someone
when you met up with Sam?

134
00:14:04,135 --> 00:14:05,554
No. No.

135
00:14:07,430 --> 00:14:08,932
I went alone.

136
00:14:10,517 --> 00:14:13,436
Did you not see anyone else in the area?

137
00:14:19,234 --> 00:14:21,111
I pushed her.

138
00:14:22,946 --> 00:14:25,490
I killed Teacher Sam.

139
00:14:34,207 --> 00:14:35,750
No, I didn't.

140
00:14:37,586 --> 00:14:39,212
I didn't notice anything either.

141
00:14:56,313 --> 00:14:57,981
-Professor Carpio!
-There!

142
00:14:58,064 --> 00:15:00,317
-Ma'am!
-We have a question!

143
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,401
Ma'am, sir, a statement, please!

144
00:15:01,484 --> 00:15:03,778
Why did the police take your statement?

145
00:15:03,862 --> 00:15:05,822
Do you have anything to do
with Sam Ignacio's death?

146
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:09,367
Ma'am, is it true that you had an affair
with Sam Ignacio?

147
00:15:13,872 --> 00:15:16,708
We have nothing to do
with Sam Ignacio's death.

148
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:19,669
We are here to cooperate. That's all.

149
00:15:19,753 --> 00:15:22,797
Our family was once a victim
of false accusations.

150
00:15:22,881 --> 00:15:26,593
We will now prove
that our family is innocent.

151
00:15:28,511 --> 00:15:31,097
-Sir, we have more questions!
-Wait, sir!

152
00:15:31,181 --> 00:15:33,224
-Ma'am, one more question!
-Don't force them!

153
00:15:33,308 --> 00:15:35,101
-Sir!
-Ma'am!

154
00:15:35,185 --> 00:15:36,811
Ma'am, do you have anything to say?

155
00:15:36,895 --> 00:15:39,773
-Sir, please wait!
-Ma'am, any words, please?

156
00:15:39,856 --> 00:15:41,524
-Sir, wait!
-Ma'am, do you have a relationship--

157
00:15:41,608 --> 00:15:43,151
Ma'am, just one statement, please!

158
00:15:43,234 --> 00:15:45,737
-Ma'am, say something!
-Ma'am, give us a statement!

159
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:49,032
-Ma'am, wait!
-Sir, please wait!

160
00:15:49,115 --> 00:15:51,576
Married teachers at a state university,

161
00:15:51,660 --> 00:15:54,454
identified as new suspects
in Sam Ignacio's murder case.

162
00:15:54,537 --> 00:15:57,749
We have nothing to do
with Sam Ignacio's death.

163
00:15:57,832 --> 00:15:59,959
We are here to cooperate. That's all.

164
00:16:00,043 --> 00:16:03,755
-Sir, wait!
-Ma'am, do you have anything to say?

165
00:16:03,838 --> 00:16:06,841
-Ma'am, say something!
-Ma'am, give us a statement!

166
00:16:08,885 --> 00:16:10,095
Again?

167
00:16:10,762 --> 00:16:12,347
What does that mean?

168
00:16:51,928 --> 00:16:53,430
You were on the news.

169
00:16:53,513 --> 00:16:57,142
What happened?

170
00:16:59,561 --> 00:17:01,146
Don't worry about that.

171
00:17:01,229 --> 00:17:03,481
What matters is that
your dad and I are here for you.

172
00:18:24,479 --> 00:18:31,027
Eli, why did you push me? Why?

173
00:19:40,638 --> 00:19:41,806
Mrs. Carpio.

174
00:19:41,890 --> 00:19:44,392
Your son, Eli, is here at the lighthouse.

175
00:19:44,475 --> 00:19:46,728
I'll watch him until you get here.

176
00:19:51,316 --> 00:19:52,442
Oh, God, Eli.

177
00:20:26,809 --> 00:20:28,353
Teacher Sam...

178
00:20:29,062 --> 00:20:33,441
I'm sorry.

179
00:20:34,275 --> 00:20:36,653
I didn't mean to push you.

180
00:20:39,155 --> 00:20:41,866
I didn't mean to hurt you.

181
00:20:46,329 --> 00:20:49,207
You were my friend...

182
00:20:50,249 --> 00:20:53,002
My favorite teacher.

183
00:20:55,046 --> 00:20:56,422
Please forgive me.

184
00:20:57,757 --> 00:20:59,884
I'm sorry.

185
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:03,972
You said I'm brave.

186
00:21:04,055 --> 00:21:05,807
You said I'm strong.

187
00:21:06,724 --> 00:21:08,643
But I'm not...

188
00:21:08,726 --> 00:21:11,104
I pushed you. I killed you.

189
00:21:11,896 --> 00:21:13,940
And I lied.

190
00:21:19,612 --> 00:21:21,364
Teacher Sam...

191
00:21:23,116 --> 00:21:28,705
I miss you every day.

192
00:21:41,676 --> 00:21:42,760
Eli.

193
00:21:42,844 --> 00:21:43,803
Son.

194
00:21:44,554 --> 00:21:46,389
Back up a bit, you might fall.

195
00:21:47,098 --> 00:21:47,932
Come here.

196
00:21:48,391 --> 00:21:50,601
Come here, all right?

197
00:21:51,644 --> 00:21:52,645
Come on.

198
00:21:53,146 --> 00:21:54,564
It's all right, come here.

199
00:21:54,939 --> 00:21:55,982
Come on.

200
00:22:14,792 --> 00:22:16,586
It's okay...

201
00:22:16,669 --> 00:22:18,337
Hey, son.

202
00:22:24,969 --> 00:22:26,471
Eli, just relax...

203
00:22:26,554 --> 00:22:32,060
Please, don't punish my mama and papa.

204
00:22:34,604 --> 00:22:38,691
They didn't do anything wrong.

205
00:22:38,775 --> 00:22:41,069
It's me. It's my fault.

206
00:22:41,152 --> 00:22:44,030
Eli, dear, I'm really sorry,
but I can't understand you.

207
00:22:44,113 --> 00:22:49,827
Teacher Sam fell because of me.

208
00:23:01,339 --> 00:23:03,257
Eli!

209
00:23:04,509 --> 00:23:05,802
Eli!

210
00:23:07,136 --> 00:23:08,346
Eli!

211
00:23:11,849 --> 00:23:13,935
Eli, my baby!

212
00:23:24,237 --> 00:23:26,948
Why did you come here, son?

213
00:23:27,532 --> 00:23:30,368
I'm sorry, Ma. I'm sorry.

214
00:23:32,370 --> 00:23:34,580
It's okay. It's okay.

215
00:23:35,081 --> 00:23:38,960
I was on my way to your place
when I saw him come here.

216
00:23:41,337 --> 00:23:43,381
Ma, please, tell the truth.

217
00:23:43,464 --> 00:23:48,427
-Tell the truth.
-Stop. Please stop.

218
00:23:49,220 --> 00:23:50,054
Ma...

219
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:52,598
What is Eli talking about?

220
00:23:54,684 --> 00:23:55,893
Pa, what's the truth?

221
00:23:56,561 --> 00:23:58,396
What? Are you still hiding
something from us?

222
00:24:02,817 --> 00:24:06,028
It's my fault. It's my fault.

223
00:24:10,366 --> 00:24:11,784
Please...

224
00:24:14,078 --> 00:24:15,288
Please.

225
00:24:19,167 --> 00:24:21,377
Yes, Eli. What is it?

226
00:24:22,420 --> 00:24:23,546
Sam...

227
00:24:23,629 --> 00:24:24,797
Sam...

228
00:24:25,882 --> 00:24:27,049
Sam...

229
00:24:27,133 --> 00:24:28,259
Sam?

230
00:24:28,801 --> 00:24:30,595
Teacher Sam? Yeah?

231
00:24:31,262 --> 00:24:32,263
What about her?

232
00:24:32,930 --> 00:24:34,515
I pushed her.

233
00:24:35,558 --> 00:24:36,767
Eli...

234
00:24:36,851 --> 00:24:39,604
Wait, slow down. I can't understand you.

235
00:24:39,979 --> 00:24:42,899
Teacher Sam fell.

236
00:24:44,317 --> 00:24:46,861
It's my fault. I pushed her.

237
00:24:52,450 --> 00:24:54,202
You pushed Teacher Sam?

238
00:24:55,119 --> 00:24:56,412
It's my fault.

239
00:24:59,916 --> 00:25:01,667
Don't, please.

240
00:25:02,335 --> 00:25:04,086
Please.

241
00:25:04,170 --> 00:25:06,047
Please spare my son.

242
00:25:07,506 --> 00:25:09,842
It was an accident.

243
00:25:10,718 --> 00:25:12,470
He didn't mean to.

244
00:25:13,930 --> 00:25:16,515
It was an accident. Please.

245
00:25:17,558 --> 00:25:21,395
Chief, I'm begging you.
Please spare my son.

246
00:25:21,479 --> 00:25:22,813
Please...

247
00:25:22,897 --> 00:25:24,941
That's enough! That's enough.

248
00:25:25,566 --> 00:25:26,400
That's enough.

249
00:25:30,446 --> 00:25:32,448
No, no.

250
00:25:32,531 --> 00:25:34,992
It's not your fault, okay?

251
00:25:35,076 --> 00:25:36,577
You're innocent.

252
00:25:38,246 --> 00:25:39,413
It was me!

253
00:25:40,998 --> 00:25:42,416
It was Papa.

254
00:25:42,500 --> 00:25:45,211
Papa killed Sam.

255
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:47,588
Papa killed Sam, okay?

256
00:25:48,381 --> 00:25:49,715
That's true!

257
00:25:49,799 --> 00:25:51,425
I saw her there.

258
00:25:51,509 --> 00:25:53,010
I saw her alive.

259
00:25:54,053 --> 00:25:54,887
Eli...

260
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:57,431
I saw her alive there.

261
00:25:58,099 --> 00:25:59,267
I saw her, over there.

262
00:26:00,559 --> 00:26:02,520
I saw her hanging on.

263
00:26:03,396 --> 00:26:04,230
Eli...

264
00:26:05,898 --> 00:26:06,732
It was me.

265
00:26:09,193 --> 00:26:10,528
I killed Sam.

266
00:26:33,759 --> 00:26:35,094
Help!

267
00:26:35,970 --> 00:26:37,805
Please! Somebody!

268
00:26:42,601 --> 00:26:45,563
Help me!

269
00:26:50,192 --> 00:26:51,861
We had a...

270
00:26:54,613 --> 00:26:56,782
We had a fight that night, Jackie.

271
00:27:01,662 --> 00:27:03,789
We've talked about this, haven't we?

272
00:27:03,873 --> 00:27:05,958
I don't want to make major decisions!

273
00:27:06,042 --> 00:27:07,877
That's the only thing I asked!

274
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,837
Is going on vacation a major decision?

275
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:12,506
Well, for you,
this is just a vacation, but--

276
00:27:12,590 --> 00:27:13,758
If you don't want to, then don't.

277
00:27:13,841 --> 00:27:15,426
All right, then! Forget about it!

278
00:27:16,260 --> 00:27:17,803
What I'm trying to say is,

279
00:27:17,887 --> 00:27:21,015
I'm just telling you
why I feel disappointed.

280
00:27:21,098 --> 00:27:23,434
You should've talked to me
or asked me first.

281
00:27:23,517 --> 00:27:25,770
We could've talked about it!

282
00:27:25,853 --> 00:27:29,607
Just admit it.
I can't make you happy anymore.

283
00:27:29,690 --> 00:27:31,400
Even your own kids

284
00:27:31,484 --> 00:27:33,903
-can't make you happy anymore!
-Anton!

285
00:27:33,986 --> 00:27:35,863
What? Isn't it true?

286
00:27:35,946 --> 00:27:38,282
I know where this is going. Can we just--

287
00:28:00,137 --> 00:28:03,599
How was your session with Teacher Sam?

288
00:28:05,434 --> 00:28:07,436
Maybe to you, it's nothing serious.

289
00:28:09,647 --> 00:28:11,607
But to me,

290
00:28:11,690 --> 00:28:13,984
every time we argue over a small thing,

291
00:28:14,068 --> 00:28:16,612
it makes me feel like you're gone.

292
00:28:16,695 --> 00:28:18,572
Like I'm nothing to you.

293
00:28:19,407 --> 00:28:21,784
Like you had checked out
of our life together.

294
00:28:23,035 --> 00:28:24,245
Because of her.

295
00:28:25,329 --> 00:28:27,373
Because you love Sam more than me.

296
00:28:35,381 --> 00:28:38,843
So when I got home
and saw your car was missing,

297
00:28:38,926 --> 00:28:41,220
I thought you were
meeting up with her again.

298
00:28:54,191 --> 00:28:55,484
Help!

299
00:28:55,985 --> 00:28:57,278
Help me!

300
00:28:58,487 --> 00:28:59,447
Please!

301
00:29:00,865 --> 00:29:01,740
Anybody!

302
00:29:03,492 --> 00:29:05,369
Help-- Anton!

303
00:29:05,453 --> 00:29:06,787
Sam!

304
00:29:06,871 --> 00:29:08,122
Anton, help me! Please!

305
00:29:08,998 --> 00:29:10,374
Help me, please.

306
00:29:12,751 --> 00:29:13,627
Sam!

307
00:29:14,336 --> 00:29:16,380
Grab my hand, hurry.

308
00:29:16,464 --> 00:29:17,506
Grab my hand!

309
00:29:18,215 --> 00:29:19,592
Come on, hurry!

310
00:29:22,636 --> 00:29:23,679
Grab on.

311
00:29:24,305 --> 00:29:25,222
I got you.

312
00:29:25,306 --> 00:29:26,932
I got her, Jackie.

313
00:29:28,517 --> 00:29:30,478
She shouldn't have fallen.

314
00:29:32,563 --> 00:29:34,482
I could've saved her.

315
00:29:35,608 --> 00:29:36,650
But...

316
00:29:40,154 --> 00:29:41,947
I know that I love you.

317
00:29:42,031 --> 00:29:43,949
I'm happy with you.

318
00:29:44,033 --> 00:29:45,826
I'm content being with you.

319
00:29:47,119 --> 00:29:48,704
That feeling…

320
00:29:48,787 --> 00:29:51,248
I can't feel it whenever I'm with Anton.

321
00:29:57,171 --> 00:29:58,506
I remembered what you said.

322
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:03,093
I thought, if I let Sam live,
she'd take you away from me.

323
00:30:03,969 --> 00:30:05,513
Anton...

324
00:30:05,596 --> 00:30:08,557
If I let her live,
I'd lose you completely.

325
00:30:10,976 --> 00:30:14,563
How could I save a person
who would ruin my family?

326
00:30:14,647 --> 00:30:15,898
Tell me!

327
00:30:18,609 --> 00:30:19,818
So I made a decision.

328
00:30:29,995 --> 00:30:31,622
Jackie, I let her go.

329
00:31:07,700 --> 00:31:08,784
Eli...

330
00:31:11,495 --> 00:31:12,997
It wasn't your fault.

331
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:14,456
You're innocent.

332
00:31:17,376 --> 00:31:18,752
It was me.

333
00:31:21,046 --> 00:31:23,007
I killed Sam.

334
00:31:35,352 --> 00:31:37,354
Please, please, please…

335
00:31:38,689 --> 00:31:40,190
Please forgive Papa.

336
00:31:45,404 --> 00:31:48,782
Never blame yourself, okay?

337
00:31:48,866 --> 00:31:50,826
Don't blame yourself.

338
00:31:50,909 --> 00:31:52,911
It was me! Blame me!

339
00:31:52,995 --> 00:31:54,705
I killed Sam!

340
00:31:54,788 --> 00:31:56,624
I did it!

341
00:32:24,777 --> 00:32:26,570
Put that in the hallway.

342
00:32:26,654 --> 00:32:27,571
Yes, ma'am.

343
00:32:34,370 --> 00:32:36,580
Thank you, Chief.

344
00:32:36,664 --> 00:32:38,123
This was not an easy job.

345
00:32:38,207 --> 00:32:43,045
It wasn't easy to expose
Mayor Dominguez's corruption.

346
00:32:43,671 --> 00:32:45,297
I feel bad for Ms. Ignacio.

347
00:32:45,964 --> 00:32:49,301
He used her and Able Hearts
to steal funds.

348
00:32:49,385 --> 00:32:53,430
That's why he wanted to
close her case quickly.

349
00:32:53,514 --> 00:32:55,557
So he could save himself
from getting found out

350
00:32:55,641 --> 00:32:57,851
in case the investigation got to him.

351
00:32:58,394 --> 00:33:00,396
If Ted Ignacio hadn't flipped,

352
00:33:01,021 --> 00:33:02,856
we wouldn't have been able to prove it.

353
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:04,650
Thank you, Governor.

354
00:33:04,733 --> 00:33:05,818
Thank you.

355
00:33:07,152 --> 00:33:09,029
-Gov.
-Thank you.

356
00:33:12,074 --> 00:33:13,033
Chief.

357
00:33:18,330 --> 00:33:19,873
Sam left this behind.

358
00:33:20,749 --> 00:33:24,128
Now we know who she meant to give it to.

359
00:33:39,059 --> 00:33:40,477
…but they don't last forever.

360
00:33:43,355 --> 00:33:44,857
What I'm going to do will be painful,

361
00:33:44,940 --> 00:33:47,359
but this is the only right thing to do.

362
00:34:36,617 --> 00:34:38,660
Carpio, you have a visitor.

363
00:34:55,594 --> 00:34:57,554
Thank you all for being here.

364
00:35:01,809 --> 00:35:03,310
Oh, it's my favorite.

365
00:35:05,229 --> 00:35:08,065
Did you help your mama prepare all this?

366
00:35:14,154 --> 00:35:15,280
Yes, Pa.

367
00:35:21,036 --> 00:35:22,704
How are you guys?

368
00:35:23,247 --> 00:35:24,832
How's therapy?

369
00:35:31,338 --> 00:35:32,673
It's going well.

370
00:35:33,298 --> 00:35:37,052
They said we're showing signs
of improvement.

371
00:35:39,096 --> 00:35:41,557
Eli is sleeping much better now.

372
00:35:42,516 --> 00:35:45,644
And his paintings
are gaining their color again.

373
00:35:46,812 --> 00:35:50,774
Once we move in, he's getting
a new juvenile officer to monitor him.

374
00:35:54,778 --> 00:35:57,030
How are you, son?

375
00:35:58,907 --> 00:36:00,242
I'm okay.

376
00:36:10,627 --> 00:36:13,422
I cooked it myself.

377
00:36:23,807 --> 00:36:28,353
You still haven't taught me

378
00:36:28,437 --> 00:36:33,275
your "master chef" scrambled eggs.

379
00:36:33,775 --> 00:36:36,236
I'll teach you when I get out.

380
00:36:42,618 --> 00:36:44,077
Matteo, Pia...

381
00:36:44,703 --> 00:36:46,496
When I get out,

382
00:36:48,290 --> 00:36:49,499
can I come visit you?

383
00:36:58,717 --> 00:36:59,676
Yes, Pa.

384
00:37:06,850 --> 00:37:08,101
Yeah.

385
00:37:23,492 --> 00:37:25,243
Say goodbye to your father.

386
00:37:55,941 --> 00:37:57,985
Matt, drive carefully.

387
00:38:00,779 --> 00:38:02,447
For them.

388
00:38:09,746 --> 00:38:13,750
I'll wait for you.

389
00:38:38,442 --> 00:38:39,693
Wait for me outside.

390
00:38:39,776 --> 00:38:40,944
Okay, Ma.

391
00:38:53,582 --> 00:38:55,542
Thank you for bringing them here, Jackie.

392
00:38:58,295 --> 00:38:59,880
They need this too.

393
00:39:01,381 --> 00:39:03,967
I don't know how I'll make up
for everything that's happened.

394
00:39:05,260 --> 00:39:06,553
Well...

395
00:39:06,636 --> 00:39:08,930
You can't, Anton.

396
00:39:09,598 --> 00:39:10,807
What you've done...

397
00:39:12,059 --> 00:39:13,602
can never be erased.

398
00:39:15,854 --> 00:39:17,314
But with your confession,

399
00:39:18,356 --> 00:39:19,858
for the very first time,

400
00:39:21,318 --> 00:39:23,111
you fixed something.

401
00:39:27,491 --> 00:39:29,743
Sometimes, we make

402
00:39:31,119 --> 00:39:32,996
bad decisions in life.

403
00:39:33,830 --> 00:39:35,999
Decisions we can't take back.

404
00:39:37,709 --> 00:39:39,503
And we can't erase.

405
00:39:41,004 --> 00:39:45,717
But we also have the power
to do what's right.

406
00:40:06,279 --> 00:40:09,241
For the longest time,
we were trapped in silence.

407
00:40:11,159 --> 00:40:14,204
We thought it would fix our broken family.

408
00:40:15,330 --> 00:40:16,540
But it didn't.

409
00:40:20,210 --> 00:40:22,045
It's what destroyed us.

410
00:40:26,591 --> 00:40:29,094
But breaking that silence

411
00:40:30,804 --> 00:40:31,972
is all it took.

412
00:40:33,515 --> 00:40:35,767
It's the truth that set us free.

413
00:40:37,727 --> 00:40:39,604
And that truth,

414
00:40:40,814 --> 00:40:44,484
I believe, is what'll give us peace.

415
00:40:46,444 --> 00:40:49,364
Peace, not just for our family,

416
00:40:51,199 --> 00:40:53,910
but for all of our consciences.

417
00:41:09,968 --> 00:41:11,011
Anton!

418
00:41:11,094 --> 00:41:13,471
Anton, help me, please!

419
00:41:13,555 --> 00:41:16,016
Sam, grab my hand!

420
00:41:17,309 --> 00:41:18,935
Grab my hand, hurry!

421
00:41:19,019 --> 00:41:21,104
Come on, hurry!

422
00:41:34,701 --> 00:41:35,785
Sam!

423
00:42:13,073 --> 00:42:14,908
Here, Matt.

424
00:42:14,991 --> 00:42:16,076
I got it.

425
00:42:17,327 --> 00:42:19,079
Here you go. Ma...

426
00:42:19,162 --> 00:42:20,413
This too.

427
00:42:24,501 --> 00:42:25,335
It's all good.

428
00:42:50,902 --> 00:42:51,945
Well?

429
00:42:52,570 --> 00:42:53,655
Shall we go?

430
00:43:26,771 --> 00:43:27,897
Let's go.

431
00:45:50,874 --> 00:45:52,750
Love is only sweet at the beginning.

432
00:45:55,462 --> 00:45:57,297
It's only fun at the start.

433
00:45:59,340 --> 00:46:02,177
We think love will complete us.

434
00:46:06,639 --> 00:46:09,392
But it will only ruin our lives.

435
00:46:14,898 --> 00:46:16,024
I'll just go there to work.

436
00:46:16,107 --> 00:46:17,734
When I get back,
our lives will be much better.

437
00:46:36,377 --> 00:46:37,504
Let's get out of here.

438
00:46:37,587 --> 00:46:39,339
If we stay here in Morocco,

439
00:46:39,422 --> 00:46:42,050
we'll have to keep hiding
like rats from those demons.

440
00:46:42,133 --> 00:46:44,219
-Did you see the thief's face?
-No.

441
00:46:44,302 --> 00:46:45,428
Excuse me.

442
00:46:46,095 --> 00:46:47,388
What's your problem?

443
00:46:48,723 --> 00:46:49,891
I don't understand!

444
00:46:54,354 --> 00:46:56,231
Your mom is in the hospital.

445
00:46:56,940 --> 00:46:57,857
You're Filipino?

446
00:46:59,734 --> 00:47:01,694
Where there's money, that's where I go.

447
00:47:01,778 --> 00:47:03,404
We're both just trying to make a living.

448
00:47:03,488 --> 00:47:05,573
We're different. You're a good person.

449
00:47:10,537 --> 00:47:12,330
Go to the hotel. The sheikh is there.

450
00:47:12,413 --> 00:47:14,791
Everything will be expensive.

451
00:47:14,874 --> 00:47:17,126
Gold, diamonds, everything.

452
00:47:17,502 --> 00:47:20,421
After this mission, we can finally leave.

453
00:47:21,548 --> 00:47:23,466
-Who are you, really?
-You don't know anything.

454
00:47:23,550 --> 00:47:25,677
Of course, I don't!
You made a fool out of me!

455
00:47:40,358 --> 00:47:41,192
Chameleon!

456
00:47:41,609 --> 00:47:42,443
Run!

457
00:47:45,989 --> 00:47:46,823
Freeze!

458
00:47:50,743 --> 00:47:51,578
Teo!

459
00:47:56,332 --> 00:47:57,166
Yana!
